% --- Section 1: Defining Competition ---
\textbf{Understanding the Competitive Field} \\
Amazon Prime doesn't just compete with one type of company; it battles for a share of the customer's time, wallet, and lifestyle across multiple industries.

\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=1.5em]
    \item \textbf{Direct Competitors:} These are the "head-to-head" rivals who offer the exact same services, such as streaming movies or digital music.
    \item \textbf{Indirect Competitors:} These are the "alternative" rivals who offer different services (like food delivery or shopping rewards) that still compete for the same monthly subscription budget.
\end{itemize}

\vspace{0.4cm}

% --- Direct Competitors Section ---
\begin{tikzpicture}
\node[fill=amazonblue, text=white, font=\large\bfseries, minimum width=\linewidth, inner sep=6pt, align=left, rounded corners=2pt] {
    DIRECT COMPETITORS: THE BATTLE FOR SCREEN TIME
};
\end{tikzpicture}

\vspace{0.2cm}

\textbf{1. Netflix - The Content Specialist} \\
While Prime offers shopping, Netflix focuses entirely on being the best at storytelling. It is the go-to for people who prioritize high-quality original series and movies over shopping perks.

\textbf{2. Disney+ Hotstar - The Live Experience} \\
This is the major rival for sports fans and families. By bundling live cricket and regional shows, it captures the audience that values "appointment viewing" and live events.

\vspace{0.5cm}

% --- Indirect Competitors Section ---
\begin{tikzpicture}
\node[fill=smileorange, text=white, font=\large\bfseries, minimum width=\linewidth, inner sep=6pt, align=left, rounded corners=2pt] {
    INDIRECT COMPETITORS: THE BATTLE FOR CONVENIENCE
};
\end{tikzpicture}

\vspace{0.2cm}

\textbf{3. Flipkart Plus - The Retail Alternative} \\
Flipkart focuses on the "shopper first." While it doesn't have a massive movie library, its reward-based loyalty program attracts those who just want the best deals and fastest shipping on products.

\textbf{4. Swiggy One - The Daily Essential} \\
Swiggy competes for "subscription space." A customer might choose food delivery perks over video streaming if their daily priority is saving money on meals and groceries rather than watching a movie.
